Title: Smart Occupancy Detection and Alert System
Objective
Build a real-time occupancy monitoring system that detects the number of people present in a
live video feed using object detection, and automatically sends an email alert when the count
exceeds 4 people.

Background
This assignment does not introduce new tools. It requires combining the components you have
already built in earlier class projects:
● Object detection with YOLO (used in the PPE Safety Compliance project)
● Flask backend serving a video feed (used in the PPE Safety Compliance project)
● HTML frontend displaying the live feed (used in the PPE Safety Compliance project)
● Automated Gmail alerts using app passwords (used in the Gmail Automation module)

Requirements
Object Detection
● Use any object detection model to detect and count the person class in each
frame of a live or recorded video feed
● Apply confidence thresholding to filter unreliable detections
● Maintain a running count of people detected in the current frame

Backend (Flask)
● Load the object detection model and process the video stream frame by frame
● Expose the live video feed to the frontend
● Expose the current occupancy count to the frontend
● Trigger the alert logic when the occupancy threshold is exceeded

